headline: DaVita HealthCare (DVA) Beats Q4 Earnings and Revenue Estimates
summary: DaVita HealthCare (DVA) delivered earnings and revenue surprises of 1.36% and 1.22%, respectively, for the quarter ended December 2024. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?

headline: DaVita (NYSE:DVA) Posts Better-Than-Expected Sales In Q4 But Stock Drops
summary: Dialysis provider DaVita Inc. (NYSE:DVA) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2024, with sales up 4.7% year on year to $3.29 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.24 per share was 4.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: DaVita HealthCare: Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The kidney dialysis provider posted revenue of $3.29 billion in the period. For the year, the company reported profit of $936.3 million, or $10.73 per share. Revenue was reported as $12.82 billion.
